pullRequest.title: Version up after azure core release.
pullRequest.bodyText:
We have released azure core 1.2.0, So we version up for next release.
All the SDK libraries uses released version of core.
Also removed "unreleased_" tag.
Used script .\eng\versioning\pom_file_version_scanner.ps1 to validate.

commit.message: Version up after azure core release. Validate via pom_file_version_scanner.ps1

nodes.bodyText: Should revert all the README changes, this hasn't been released yet and we don't want to accidentally release all the READMEs with non-existent versions.
nodes.diffHunk:
@@ -37,7 +37,7 @@ AppConfiguration to use Netty HTTP client.
 <dependency>
     <groupId>com.azure</groupId>
     <artifactId>azure-core-http-netty</artifactId>
-    <version>1.2.0</version>
+    <version>1.3.0-beta.1</version>

nodes.bodyText: Same as other comment about README versions.

-  <version>1.1.0</version>
+  <version>1.2.0-beta.1</version>

commit.message: reming version up in README,  since they are not released yet.

nodes.bodyText: Hemant, with 1.1.0 being just released, the azure-core-test's current version should be 1.2.0-beta.1 to keep it in line with the other version increments.

nodes.bodyText: If we're holding off on updating the versions then just run the script again with the --sr option to skip the readme updates. Though, with that being said, were the readme versions for the artifacts we're releasing correct before the release of those respective artifacts.
